name: Gull
description: Loathsome Oils Series | The Ring-billed Gulls are kinda like Herring Gull minions, where one seagull makes the first move on your sandwich at the beach, and the others pile on.  That said, there's a fierce beauty and sleekness to these gulls that I've always appreciated. | Photographed January 14, 2021 in Windsor Locks, CT.
